<F P=102>   AU0504134794 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0504134794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Today, the first session of the Executive 
Committee of the Party of Democratic Action [SDA] was held after 
its number was filled at the last convention of the party on 25 
and 26 March. 
  The implementation of the Constitution of the Federation of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina -- adopted at the recent session of the 
Constituent Assembly of the Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina -- 
was discussed, inter alia, at the session. It was concluded 
that Mr. Alija Izetbegovic should be incorporated into the 
institution of the presidency of the future federation, and he 
would have the first presidential mandate. The SDA Executive 
Committee believes that there are very significant reasons -- 
arising from political and moral interests of the Bosniak Muslim 
people -- that demand such a solution. Regional and communal 
committees of the SDA in Bosnia-Herzegovina will be informed 
about this decision. [passage omitted] 

