<H3> <TI>   Battle for Gorazde Continuing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Battle for Gorazde Continuing </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Civilian Areas Shelled </H4>

<F P=102> AU0604144694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0604144694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Enes Murtovic from Gorazde] </F>
  [Text] The siren sounding general danger (?shows) that 
there is no peace in Gorazde again today. The chetniks [words 
indistinct] are shelling civilian areas and the defense lines. 
The highest caliber shells are again destroying the Gorazde 
region that borders Foca, Cajnice, and Rogatica. In the course 
of the day, several howitzer shells landed on the town. Even 
though the residents of Gorazde are in shelters all the time, 
the casualty figures are nevertheless [passage indistinct] (?41) 
women and old men. [words indistinct] arrival of General 
Michael Rose, commander of the UN forces in Bosnia-Herzegovina, 
separated the chetniks from their (?deadly) weapons for only a 
moment. As we send this report, explosions are once again being 
heard in the town's suburbs. The chetniks are also attacking 
the town itself. 
  The [word indistinct] and the suffering of the population in 
the protected zone of Gorazde is continuing before the eyes of 
the international community, which again is not taking [word 
indistinct] measures to stop the latest offensive by the 
chetniks. 
  This is Enes Murtovic reporting for Radio and Television 
Bosnia- Herzegovina from the Press Center of the Gorazde region. 

</TEXT>

