<H3> <TI>   Battle for Gorazde Continuing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Battle for Gorazde Continuing </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Mladic on Talks With Rose </H4>

<F P=102> LD0604151194 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1351 GMT 6 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0604151194 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, 6 Apr (TANJUG) -- The commander of the 
main headquarters of the Srpska republic army, general Ratko 
Mladic, said today that "the Muslims' mad venture in the Gorazde 
area has failed". 
  "I hope that they have learned a lesson," Mladic said. 
Explaining the talks today with General Michael Rose, the 
UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces] commander for former 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, Mladic stressed in a statement for TANJUG 
that an agreement had been reached to send some military 
observers to Gorazde. 
  We suggested to Rose that he organize a meeting of the 
warring sides because we have nothing to discuss with them, 
either about Gorazde or about anything else. We are not at war 
with UNPROFOR, but we are open to discussion on all issues, 
including the discussion of Gorazde with the Muslim side, with 
UNPROFOR's mediation, general Mladic said. 

</TEXT>

