<H3> <TI>   Battle for Gorazde Continuing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Battle for Gorazde Continuing </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    UN Observers Arrive </H4>

<F P=102> AU0704101894 Paris AFP in English 0928 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0704101894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, April 7 (AFP) -- A team of 11 UN 
observers and liaison officers arrived in the eastern Bosnian 
Moslem enclave of Gorazde Thursday, a United Nations spokesman 
said. 
  UN Protection Force (UNPROFOR) spokesman Major Rob Annink 
said eight armed UNPROFOR officers and three unarmed military 
observers had reached the enclave, where more than 60 people are 
reported to have died since a Bosnian Serb offensive began 10 
days ago. 
  The team, which set out from Sarajevo, was stopped by Serb 
forces at Rogatica, around 40 kilometres (25 miles) from 
Gorazde, the spokesman said. 
  They were held up for several hours for administrative 
formalities despite having received all necessary authorisation, 
Annink said. 

</TEXT>

