<H3> <TI>   Battle for Gorazde Continuing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Battle for Gorazde Continuing </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    UN: `Gorazde No Longer Under Attack' </H4>

<F P=102> AU0604165794 Paris AFP in English 1637 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0604165794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] United Nations, April 6 (AFP) -- Bosnian Serbs 
besieging the Moslem enclave of Gorazde in Bosnia-Herzegovina 
stopped their shelling late Wednesday [6 April], a UN spokesman 
said Wednesday. 
  "Gorazde is no longer under attack since 1800 local time," 
the spokesman, Joe Sills said. 
  Sills said that the UN representative in Bosnia Yasushi 
Akashi had received assurance from the Bosnian Serbs that the 
attacks would not resume. 

</TEXT>

