<H3> <TI>   Serb-Muslim, Inter-Muslim Fighting Resumes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serb-Muslim, Inter-Muslim Fighting Resumes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0604223394 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 2200 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0604223394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The 59th day of the Serb aggressor's offensive on 
the Bihac region was marked by fresh attacks on civilian 
targets, industrial areas, and defense lines. The industrial 
area in Bihac was hit by a number of artillery shells and one 
woman was killed. The Serb aggressor shelled defense lines on 
Mount Grabez and the Grmusa-Srbljani plateau throughout the day. 
However, the soldiers of our army destroyed yet another 
aggressor tank in an energetic counterattack. 
  Members of the paramilitary units of the so-called Kladusa 
Autonomy [Autonomous Province of Western Bosnia -- declared by 
Fikret Abdic] used mortars to shell the Cazin municipality [area 
loyal to Izetbegovic]. One person was killed and another one 
seriously wounded. 

</TEXT>

