<H3> <TI>   Karadzic Order on Investigating Prijedor </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Karadzic Order on Investigating Prijedor </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0304182294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1730 GMT 3 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0304182294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 3 Apr (TANJUG) -- President of the Srpska 
republic [RS] Radovan Karadzic today issued an order to all 
bodies of the Ministry of Internal Affairs, military security 
bodies, and control points in the RS to urgently investigate the 
crimes in Prijedor and to secure full safety and freedom of 
movement of personnel of the International Committee of the Red 
Cross [ICRC]. 
  The order, forwarded to TANJUG, says: 
  In keeping with our obligations to international 
humanitarian 
law I order the following: 
  To take all necessary measures to investigate crimes 
committed in the Srpska republic, particularly in Prijedor; 
  To take all other actions needed to suppress extremism and 
secure the safety of members of national minorities who wish to 
stay in our republic; 
  To remove all administrative obstacles to free movement of 
civilians who wish to leave in an operation organized by the 
ICRC; 
  To secure police escort for all ICRC convoys, especially in 
the Prijedor area; 
  All our bodies have the duty to provide full safety for ICRC 
personnel and civilians who decide to leave the RS under ICRC 
protection. Any objections to the conduct of the ICRC personnel 
must not be used as a pretext to threaten their safety. The 
office of the president of the republic is to be informed about 
any objections to the ICRC's conduct; 
  To secure free passage across the Srpska republic borders to 
all ICRC convoys announced in advance and to exercise routine 
control; 
  Failure to comply or fully to comply with the order entails 
the highest degree of accountability. 
  A copy of the order will be forwarded to the ICRC to be used 
at checkpoints to avoid any possible misunderstandings. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

