<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Marjanovic on New Budget Law </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister Marjanovic on New Budget Law </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0604200994 Belgrade RTB Television Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1730 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0604200994 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade RTB Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Serbian Prime Minister Mirko Marjanovic by </F>
Ivica Milosavljevic in Belgrade on 6 April -- recorded] 
  [Text] [Milosavljevic] The proposal of the law on budget 
was endorsed at the session of the Republican Government today. 
We asked Mr. Mirko Marjanovic to give an exclusive statement on 
the occasion for the Radio and Television of Serbia. 
  [Marjanovic] Well, this is as follows: The proposal of the 
law on the budget of the Republic of Serbia for 1994 was drafted 
in conformity with the basic program of monetary reconstruction 
and the strategy of economic development of the country, and 
particularly in conformity with the government program adopted 
at the latest session of the Serbian Assembly when the 
Government was approved. One should also stress here that, 
according to the proposal of the law on the budget for 1994, 
public spending in Serbia is lower by more than 30 percent 
compared to the planned level of public spending in the 
consolidated balance on the level of the country. Now here is 
what that means: That means that the planned deficit in the 
basic program has been reduced from 1.9 billion dinars to 780 
million and we can claim with full confidence that we have 
completely realistic sources of income for covering this budget 
deficit. We can also claim with confidence that with this 
reduction of public spending by almost two-thirds we have 
established a basis for a normal program and for the realization 
of the program of economic recovery of the country. 
  I can also stress here that the social program for Serbia 
was 
also included in the budget and that with the basic principles 
and strategy of the budget established in this way, we in fact 
enabled the further removal of the burden on the economy and 
citizens, which should also be pointed out. 

</TEXT>

