<H3> <TI>   Renewal Movement Predicts Early Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Renewal Movement Predicts Early Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704115294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1057 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0704115294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 7 Apr (TANJUG) -- Ivan Kovacevic, 
spokesman of the Serbian Renewal Movement [SPO], said in a 
statement for TANJUG today that it is quite possible that 
federal elections will be held, and added that he believes it 
will be soon. 
  Kovacevic believes this will be "yet another trick" of the 
Socialist Party of Serbia which, he believes, wants to retain 
the existing, completely unjust electoral system. 
  "The Socialists would like to use this move to prolong their 
authority, despite the fact that two-thirds of Serbia's citizens 
do not vote for them," the SPO spokesman said. 

</TEXT>

