<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Olechowski Says Road to EU Difficult, Uncertain </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Olechowski Says Road to EU Difficult, Uncertain </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704090094 Warsaw PAP in Polish 0747 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0704090094 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 7 Apr--Foreign Minister Andrzej Olechowski 
said in the Sejm today that Poland might get the status of a 
European Union [EU] member in about 2000. According to him, the 
road to the EU will be long, difficult, and uncertain. 
  The minister presented the reasons behind Poland's decision 
to strive for EU membership. He said that he will hand an 
application for membership to the Greek foreign minister in 
Athens tomorrow. 
  The minister said a sounding among 12 EU members indicates 
favorable reception of Poland's application. He added that over 
70 percent of Poles favor Poland's membership in the EU. 
  According to the Polish Government, Poland meets the EU 
conditions for membership application. These conditions are: 
the existence of stable democratic institutions, the observance 
of human rights, the rule of law and order, legislation being 
adapted to EU standards, and a market economy. 

</TEXT>

