<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Maritime Minister Introduces Flag of Convenience </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Maritime Minister Introduces Flag of Convenience </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0604225394 Warsaw PAP in Polish 2054 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0604225394 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Szczecin, 6 Apr--Boguslaw Liberadzki, the minister 
of transport and maritime economy, who took part on 6 April in a 
meeting of the Szczecin Maritime Lobby, has announced the 
introduction in our country of a free register of ships sailing 
under various flags. 
  In practice, this means the birth of a Polish flag of 
convenience, similar to that of Panama or Liberia, under which 
shipowners from various countries will be able to register their 
vessels. There are many who are interested in "changing the 
flag" of their ships. 

</TEXT>

