<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Akashi, Izetbegovic Statements on Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Akashi, Izetbegovic Statements on Cease-Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0604201694 Belgrade RTB Television Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1730 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0604201694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade RTB Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Before he met Radovan Karadzic in Pale, Yasushi 
Akashi met Alija Izetbegovic, leader of the Bosnian Muslims, in 
Sarajevo. Through Eurovision exchange, we received brief 
statements by Akashi and the leader of the Bosnian Muslims after 
their meeting in Sarajevo in the morning. 
  [Begin recording] [Akashi in English with superimposed 
translation in Serbo-Croatian] The attack stopped as of 1800 
yesterday. However, we have to work first on a greater UNPROFOR 
[UN Protection Forces] presence. A larger number of armored 
vehicles should be sent and General Rose will go there very soon 
-- tomorrow or the day after tomorrow. At the same time, we are 
determined to work on a general, global cease-fire, not only the 
one between Muslim and Croatian sides, but also including the 
Serbian side, so as to establish basis for a real, lasting, and 
global peace. 
  [Izetbegovic] As regards a general cease-fire, we are of the 
opinion that one should place the surrender of heavy weaponry in 
the center of the question. In our opinion, there will be no 
peace without that. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

