<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Representatives of Bosnia, Herceg-Bosna Meet </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Representatives of Bosnia, Herceg-Bosna Meet </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0604185494 Zagreb HTV Television in Serbo-Croatian 1730 
GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0604185494 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb HTV Television </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Government representatives of Bosnia-Herzegovina and 
the Croat republic of Herceg-Bosna met for the first time in 
Mostar today. Jadranko Prlic, prime minister of Herceg-Bosna, 
and Edi Bukvic, deputy prime minister of Bosnia-Herzegovina, and 
others spoke mostly about the transformation of the present 
governments and administrations into the government and other 
federal bodies. The concrete result of the talks was the 
setting up of joint expert groups which will be in charge of 
several fields and development projects. An expert group was 
also founded which will coordinate the present financial and 
customs systems of the two governments. 
  Also discussed were the reconstruction of the Sarajevo-Ploce 
railroad, posts and telecommunications, and infrastructure in 
the Mostar area. The participants also discussed the media, 
especially the responsibility of the media on both sides in the 
consolidation of peace and the restoration of trust between 
Croat and Muslim people. 

</TEXT>

