<H3> <TI>   Party Official Alleges Greek Persecution </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Party Official Alleges Greek Persecution </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0504182994 Sofia BTA in English 1739 GMT 5 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0504182994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Today" -- BTA lead] </F>
  [Excerpts] Sofia, April 5 (BTA) -- [passage omitted] The 
rights of Bulgarians in Aegean Macedonia and Thrace in Greece 
are still being violated, Stoyan Boyadzhiev, chairman of the 
extraparliamentary Internal Macedonian Revolutionary 
Organization-Union of Macedonian Societies, told a press 
conference. To support his claim, he circulated a Bulgarian 
translation of a Greek document, entitled "Instructions for the 
Assimilation of Macedonian Bulgarians." It was issued by the 
Greek State Security Service with the Ministry of Public Order 
and signed by Maj. Gen. Dimitrios Kapelaris, according to 
Boyadzhiev. The document recommends security services to ban 
the speaking of local dialects. 

</TEXT>

