<H3> <TI>   Zhelev Receives FYROM Party Leader </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zhelev Receives FYROM Party Leader </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0504161394 Sofia BTA in English 1545 GMT 5 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0504161394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sofia, April 5 (BTA) -- President Zhelyu Zhelev 
today met Mr. Ljupco Georgievski, Chairman of the Internal 
Macedonian Revolutionary Organization-Democratic Party for 
Macedonian National Unity (IMRO-DPMNU), the president's foreign 
policy adviser Kamen Velichkov said. "I cannot say there were 
any differences between the two sides," Mr. Velichkov said. The 
leader of Macedonia's [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia 
-- FYROM] major opposition parliamentary party arrived Sunday on 
an informal visit to Bulgaria at the invitation of the 
extraparliamentary Fatherland Union. 
  The Bulgarian side reminded that this country was the first 
one to recognize the sovereignty of Macedonia in January 1992 
and laid a stress on the necessity for Macedonia to get in 
closer contacts with the European structures, the president's 
adviser said. He reiterated this country's stand against the 
embargo Greece has enforced against Macedonia and said Bulgaria 
believes it does not contribute to the stability in the Balkans. 
  Dr. Zhelev expressed his desire that the two countries 
develop unselfish relations based on an equal footing. Bulgaria 
will, however, profit from the cooperation, Mr. Velichkov said. 
  The meeting between Dr. Zhelev and Mr. Georgievski was held 
without the help of an interpreter, Mr. Velichkov also said. 
  The Macedonian guest today met National Assembly Chairman 
Aleksandur Yordanov to discuss the performance of the two 
countries' parliaments. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

