<H3> <TI>   Karabashev, Georgian Official Cited </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Karabashev, Georgian Official Cited </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0604120394 Sofia BTA in English 0953 GMT 6 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0604120394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Bulgaria, Georgia Promote Trade, Economic Cooperation" -- </F>
BTA headline] 
  [Text] Sofia, April 6 (BTA) -- The Bulgarian Deputy Prime 
Minister and Minister of Trade Valentin Karabashev today 
received the First Deputy Foreign Minister of Georgia Mikhail 
Ukleba, said the Government's Press Office. 
  They discussed the legal framework of bilateral trade and 
economic cooperation, stressing that the bilateral trade and 
economic cooperation draft accord has been initialed. The 
accord envisages the signature of agreements on air, sea and 
land transport cooperation, on the avoidance of double taxation 
and on reciprocal investment protection and promotion. 
  A Bulgarian government delegation is scheduled to visit 
Tbilisi this June, said the Press Office. 
  The Georgian delegation completed their four-day visit here 
today. 
  In the course of the visit, the sides discussed matters of 
bilateral cooperation and the Black Sea Economic Zone. They 
signed a protocol on cooperation between the two Foreign 
Ministries. The Georgian diplomat delivered a message to 
Bulgarian President Zhelyu Zhelev by Georgian President Eduard 
Shevardnadze, expressing a wish to strengthen bilateral 
relations. 

</TEXT>

