<F P=103> AU0504135694 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Litomysl, East Bohemia, April 5 (CTK) -- President 
Vaclav Havel is staying at his private residence outside Prague 
to recover from a virus infection complicated by pneumonia. 
  Presidential spokesman Ladislav Spacek said the president 
was 
trying to get better in time for the meeting of Central European 
presidents taking place here April 15-16. 
  Spacek said the president was recovering as expected and had 
canceled all his plans in order to ensure he recovered 
completely. His participation in the presidential summit, 
however, depends on several medical tests which are still being 
run. 

