<H3> <TI>   Deputy Protests Treatment of Dissidents </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputy Protests Treatment of Dissidents </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0504192994 Budapest MTI in English 1500 GMT 5 Apr 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0504192994 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, April 5 (MTI) -- "They should go home!", 
opposition MP Zoltan Trombitas of the Federation of Young 
Democrats (Fidesz) shouted after Deputy Speaker of Parliament 
Vince Voros had greeted the Chinese justice minister [Xiao Yang] 
and his delegation in the box of honour at Hungarian Parliament 
today. 
  Late, after the scheduled departure of the Chinese 
delegation, Trombitas received a public warning from Voros in 
front of the plenary session. 
  Fidesz sources say Trombitas was protesting against Chinese 
treatment of dissidents, now being arrested in China, while some 
leaders of the 1989 student protests are still in prison there. 

</TEXT>

