<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Slovakia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Outlines Government Goals </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister Outlines Government Goals </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0704085494 Prague CTK in English 1853 GMT 6 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0704085494 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, April 6 (CTK) -- It is the unambiguous 
goal of the new Slovak Government to speed up the process of 
economic transformation in a way society can bear, Prime 
Minister Jozef Moravcik told the Bratislava diplomatic corps 
today. 
  Moravcik said the government would take concrete steps to 
develop the private sector, support small and medium businesses, 
increase the competitiveness of Slovak products, and create job 
opportunities. 
  He also promised that privatization would be speeded up in a 
fair way. "We welcome more active participation by foreign 
investors in the privatization process in the Slovak Republic," 
he said. 
  The government also intended to create the necessary 
conditions for the broadest possible integration of the Slovak 
economy into European and world economic structures. 
  Even though his government will only last until the 
elections 
six months from now, it would introduce innovations into the 
economy that should outlive the government's term of office, 
Moravcik said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

