<F P=101> Albania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meets With Human Rights Group </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meets With Human Rights Group </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0604172694 Tirana ATA in English 1023 GMT 6 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0604172694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Albania's Acceptance in the Council of Europe Favours the </F>
Observation of the Human Rights" -- ATA headline] 
  [Text] Tirana, April 6 (ATA) -- In the meeting of April 5 
with the delegation of the Ad Hoc Committee of the Council of 
Europe [CE], the Albanian Helsinki Committee [KShH] said that 
Albania's acceptance in the Council of Europe would favour the 
observation of the human rights and would be fruitful for the 
development of democracy. The chairman of this committee, Josif 
Vrioni, made a panorama of the work made for the rehabilitation 
of the formerly politically prisoners, establishment of the rule 
of law and the press freedom, underlining the great difficulties 
that existed in the post dictatorship period. 
  Mr. Kujtim Cashku, one of the representatives of this 
committee, said that Albania has started the observation of the 
human rights from the scratch, when there were no ministry of 
justice and specialised institutions for this purpose, there 
were no laws on the protection of the private ownership and 
other such things. 
  Asked by one of the members of the delegation of the Council 
of Europe whether there are cases of human rights violations in 
Albania, Mr. Vrioni said that the situation of human rights 
observation is not perfect, but it is generally good, stressing 
that Albania fulfills all conditions to become a full member of 
the Council of Europe. 
  With regard to the existence of an influence from the 
political forces on the decisions by lawyers, Mr. Vrioni said 
that to speak about such a thing one needs to have facts and not 
suspicions. 
  Questioned whether the Albanian Helsinki Committee insists 
in 
Albania's becoming a member of the Council of Europe, all its 
members gave an absolute unanimous positive reply. 
  Mr. Cashku handed to the European delegation a report about 
the questions of the human rights observation in Albania. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

