<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Rejects Candidacy of SLD's Rosati </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Rejects Candidacy of SLD's Rosati </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0604184494 Warsaw PAP in English 1653 GMT 6 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0604184494 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, April 6 -- The president does not change his 
mind, the presidential spokesman Andrzej Drzycimski said 
Wednesday assessing chances of Dariusz Rosati, the candidate of 
the Democratic Left Alliance [SLD], to assume the posts of 
deputy prime minister and finance minister. 
  Drzycimski said that President Lech Walesa is open to talks 
with representatives of the ruling coalition or the prime 
minister about the filling of the vacant post in the government 
but stressed that Rosati's candidature was completely out of the 
question since it had already been officially rejected by the 
president. 
  According to Drzycimski, the Thursday meeting between the 
president and the Sejm Speaker Jozef Oleksy will be devoted to 
discussing the results of a parliamentary delegation's visit 
paid recently to Moscow. 
  The spokesman said also that the president had not taken a 
decision yet whether to sign the law on election to commune 
councils. 

</TEXT>

