<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, April 6 -- European integration and 
cooperation in the Baltic region were the main topics raised by 
Polish and Finnish foreign ministers Andrzej Olechowski and 
Heikki Haavisto during their meeting Wednesday. 
  After the talks Haavisto termed to-date Polish-Finnish 
relations as good. The ministers reviewed bilateral relations 
and thought they should be broadened. 
  Discussed was the situation in the Baltic region and the 
European security as well as negotiations with the European 
Union on Finland and Poland's membership. 
  The sides also discussed Polish-Finnish cooperation in the 
Council of the Baltic Sea States, in particular the Via Baltica 
project. 

