<H3> <TI>   Molnar: SNS Leaders Knew About Moscow Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Molnar: SNS Leaders Knew About Moscow Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0704191494 Prague CTK in English 1228 GMT 7 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0704191494 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, April 6 (CTK) -- Information given to 
CTK by Slovak National Party (SNS) deputy Marian Andel 
concerning participation of SNS Deputy Chairman Juraj Molnar in 
the World Pan-Slav Congress in Moscow is erroneous, Molnar told 
CTK today. 
  On Sunday Andel said that "neither himself nor SNS honorary 
Chairman Jozef Prokes knew about Molnar's visit to Moscow to 
attend the congress organized by Russian ultra nationalist and 
Chairman of the Liberal Democratic Party (LDP) Zhirinovskiy. 
SNS Chairman Jan Slota said on Monday that Molnar was sent to 
Moscow by the SNS leadership as an observer. Molnar said that 
although Andel could not know about his visit due to illness, 
Prokes was informed about it. 
  According to unofficial announcement provided by the SNS 
today it neither had established nor intended to establish 
contacts with any liberal party as it does not share liberal 
values. Informal and unofficial consultations with LDP 
representatives could not be considered the SNS's orientation 
towards the LDP's political line just as the presence of Peter 
Weiss, chairman of the Democratic Left Party (SDL) at the 
Bratislava Central Market place cannot be considered proof of 
the SDL's inclination towards a market economy, says a SNS 
statement. 
  Molnar declined to answer the question of whether or not he 
would meet Zhirinovskiy during his anticipated visit to Slovakia. 

</TEXT>

