<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Adopts Draft Bill on 1994 Budget </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Adopts Draft Bill on 1994 Budget </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0604082494 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
0400 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0604082494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>
<F P=105>  Romanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The government met in a special session yesterday 
to discuss this year's state budget. Florin Georgescu, state 
minister and finance minister, who presented the objectives and 
the structure of the draft budget, emphasized that the current 
document reflects to a greater extent than previous bills on the 
state budget the dynamics of the reform and the goals stipulated 
by the government program, including the ones agreed with the 
IMF. The document aims to improve the structure of state 
incomes from taxation and to avoid higher taxes, as for this 
year the planned average level of taxes reaches 31 percent, 
whereas in 1993 and in 1992 that level was 32 and 35 percent 
respectively. 
  The draft budget's chapter dedicated to state spending 
stipulates the continuation of boosting investments, especially 
in the infrastructure, ensuring social protection, support for 
the agricultural producers, the decentralization of the 
activities paid from the budget, and the stimulation of exports. 
In a statement made to our reporters, the finance minister said 
that it will be an austerity budget with the strict limitation 
of state spending, especially related to personnel. 
  GNP is expected to grow by 1.5 percent compared with last 
year, whereas the budget deficit is expected to grow by 3.5 
percent, and the inflation rate by 75 percent. 
  According to information released by the government, the 
executive adopted the draft bill on the [1994] state budget with 
certain corrections that are to be applied without delay, after 
which the document will be submitted to parliament as soon as 
possible. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

