  [Text] Ljubljana, 6 Apr (TANJUG) -- The Muslim Army will 
attack Serb parts of Sarajevo if Gorazde were to fall -- DELO 
claims today, citing sources within the Muslim leadership. 
  Units of Izetbegovic's army are preparing to attack 
Grbavica, 
Vogosca, Ilidza, and other Serb-held districts of Sarajevo. 
High-ranking Muslim military officials and Izetbegovic's close 
aides have worked out a plan to attack Serb positions, 
encouraged by the fact that Serb units have no heavy weaponry in 
the area. They have been left without artillery and tanks and 
the Muslim leadership is aware of this, the Slovene daily 
stresses. 

