<H3> <TI>   Talks on Future Government Coalition Underway </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Talks on Future Government Coalition Underway </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0704172794 Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network in Slovene 
1330 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0704172794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Slovene </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] The negotiating teams of the Slovene Christian 
Democrats [SKD] and the Liberal Democracy [LDS] met this 
morning. They held an hour of consultations in view of the 
recent SKD proposal to form a government coalition of two 
parties, that is, without the United List, while the Social 
Democrats have already announced their departure from the 
government. 
  As it was expected, today's meeting did not produce any 
concrete decisions about the fate of the future government 
coalition. After the meeting of the negotiating teams of both 
parties, we can also expect a meeting of the members of the LDS 
executive council and the SDK council. The SKD will make the 
final decision about this next week and definitely before the 
annual party conference that will take place between 22 and 24 
April. 
  A segment of the party's membership demands departure from 
the coalition. However, a sober examination shows the great 
political damage that the party would suffer if it left the 
coalition at a moment when tangible results in new spheres that 
will also bring electoral points are in sight. 
  One, therefore, should not expect any more explicit 
decisions 
from the afternoon meeting of the SKD council. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

