<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition Leader Predicts Social Unrest </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Opposition Leader Predicts Social Unrest </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804093794 Warsaw PAP in Polish 0755 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0804093794 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Wroclaw, 8 Apr--New parliamentary elections are a 
foregone conclusion and will be held within a year. Any excuse 
suffices for the president to dissolve the present parliament, 
the leader of the Confederation for an Independent Poland [KPN], 
Leszek Moczulski, maintained in an interview with a SLOWO 
POLSKIE journalist on 8 April. According to him, the "KPN 
parliamentary floor group as well as several other political 
groupings in the Sejm are capable of providing the president 
with such an excuse when the time is right for them." Moczulski 
is also of the opinion that a breakup of the governing coalition 
is unavoidable. Should it happen, it will be difficult to 
establish a majority in the present Sejm. 
  The KPN leader warns that Poland is facing events similar to 
those of 1980. According to him, none of the problems put 
forward "so forcefully" then have ever been resolved. "If 
society realizes now that the confidence placed in all corners 
of the political scene, apart from the Confederation, has been 
ill-placed and that it has been let down, we are going to have 
events similar to those in August [1980]," Moczulski maintains. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

