<H3> <TI>   UN Troops Crossed Yugoslav Border `by Mistake' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Troops Crossed Yugoslav Border `by Mistake' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704111894 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 0941 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0704111894 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Skopje, 7 Apr (TANJUG) -- The UN Protection Forces 
[UNPROFOR] command in Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia -- FYROM] announced today that three UNPROFOR soldiers 
detained by the Yugoslav Army on Monday entered Federal Republic 
of Yugoslavia territory by mistake. 
  A statement said the UNPROFOR members "thought they were on 
Macedonian territory" and were taken to the Yugoslav border 
watchtower of Slavujevac "before they realized they were on FRY 
[Federal Republic of Yugoslavia] territory." 
  The statement says the blue helmets were allowed to return 
to 
Macedonia on the same day after several hours of questioning. 
  UNPROFOR sees this incident as a "minor" one, and believes 
that its members crossed into Yugoslav territory because of "the 
confusion over the exact location of the border line." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-7988 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu068_m_94004" </HT>


