<H3> <TI>   Casualties Expected </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Casualties Expected </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0704143494 Paris AFP in English 1424 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0704143494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Zagreb, April 7 (AFP) -- A series of explosions 
ripped through a munitions dump outside the Croatian capital 
Thursday [7 April], prompting the authorities to place the 
surrounding suburbs under alert and stop all traffic. 
  The dump was ablaze and shells were exploding every few 
seconds, eyewitnesses said. Residents near the munitions depot 
in Sesvete, about 12 kilometres (seven miles) outside Zagreb, 
were told to take refuge in bomb-shelters. 
  There were no immediate reports of casualties but Sesvete 
police told AFP they expected that people had been injured. 

</TEXT>

