<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Civilians Killed in Bihac </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Civilians Killed in Bihac </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704215094 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 2000 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0704215094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Five people were killed and 30 wounded, among them 
two pregnant women and several children, in the shelling of the 
Bihac area today. The town and its surrounding areas were 
shelled three times during the day. The material damage is 
vast. Hundreds of mortar and howitzer shells fell on the 
positions of the defenders on the Grmusa-Srbljani plateau and in 
Grabez. The attacks intensified in the afternoon. 
  The attacks by paramilitary formations of the so-called 
Kladusa autonomy also continued throughout the day. They fired 
on the Cazin villages of Privala, [place name indistinct] and 
Cajici, using mortars and antitank weapons. There were several 
casualties. 

</TEXT>

