<H3> <TI>   Mladic Sets Conditions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mladic Sets Conditions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0704144694 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0704144694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Marica Lalovic from Pale] </F>
  [Text] The talks between the military commanders of the 
Serbian and the Muslim sides -- General Ratko Mladic and [B-H 
Army Commander General] Rasim Delic -- which were scheduled to 
take place at Sarajevo airport yesterday, have not started yet. 
The mediator in the talks, which should result in the signing of 
a cease-fire agreement, today held talks with General Mladic and 
conveyed to him the new demands posed by the Muslim side. 
Namely, General Rose reported that Rasim Delic was making his 
arrival to the airport and the talks conditional upon the 
withdrawal of the Serbian army from all the positions around 
Gorazde to the lines held prior to the outbreak of the latest 
clashes. 
  General Mladic warned UN Protection Force Commander General 
Rose not to accept any conditions for talks and said that only 
an instantaneous halt of all combat activities on all the 
separating lines in the former Bosnia-Herzegovina can be 
discussed. 

</TEXT>

