<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mladic: Muslims Backing `War Option' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mladic: Muslims Backing `War Option' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704214294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 2058 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0704214294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, 7 Apr (TANJUG) -- Lieutenant Colonel 
General Ratko Mladic, chief of general staff of the Srpska 
republic army, said that he held two separate and very useful 
talks with General Michael Rose, UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces] 
commander for former Bosnia-Herzegovina, this evening. 
  In a statement for the Serb Sarajevo Radio, Gen. Mladic did 
not give any details of the talks, but said that "on the whole 
everything boils down to the fact that the Muslims do not want 
to sign an agreement to end of hostilities." 
  Mladic did not wish to comment on the present situation in 
the areas in which Muslim units launched an offensive. He said 
that the Muslims had smuggled units from central Bosnia into the 
area toward Gorazde and that it is obvious they are backing the 
war option. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

