<H3> <TI>   Izetbegovic, Rose Discuss Situation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Izetbegovic, Rose Discuss Situation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704221194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 2000 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0704221194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Alija Izetbegovic, president of the Presidency of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, today received General Michael Rose, the 
UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces] commander for 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. Haris Silajdzic, the prime minister of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, and General Rasim Delic, the 
Bosnia-Herzegovina army commander, were present at the talks. 
  The difficult situation in Gorazde, the town which has been 
under a strong offensive by the Serb aggressor for over a week, 
was discussed. Gen. Rose was asked to do everything within his 
powers to bring an end to the offensive and to have the 
aggressor's army return to its pre-31 March positions. 
  It is expected that Gen. Rose will again hold talks with 
President Izetbegovic tomorrow after his talks with 
representatives of the aggressor's side. 

</TEXT>

