<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   TANJUG Reports Muslim Attack </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    TANJUG Reports Muslim Attack </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804100994 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 0859 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0804100994 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Cajnice, 8 Apr (TANJUG) -- The command of the 
Srpska republic army's Herzegovina corps this morning said in a 
statement that heavy fighting had continued over the last 24 
hours in the area of Oglecevo, Vitkovici [near Gorazde] and 
Donja Potkozara. 
  The same source says that a strong attack by the Muslim army 
was repelled last night in the area of Krizevci, in the 
immediate vicinity of Gorazde. [passage omitted] 
  Over the last 24 hours the frequency of NATO flights at very 
low altitude over the area of Gorazde, Cajnice, and Foca, where 
the fighting has been under way for 11 days, has increased, the 
statement says. 
  Reinforcements in groups of 30 or 40 soldiers, specially 
trained in sabotage and terrorist activities, are being sent to 
the Muslim army in Gorazde from central Bosnia, Serb military 
sources say. 
  The fate of some 700 Serbs trapped in Gorazde is 
increasingly 
uncertain, in the light of the fact that they are being used by 
the Muslims as a shield for Muslim soldiers who are being 
forcibly sent to the front line, the statement says. 

</TEXT>

