<DATE1>  7 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mostar Opens Checkpoint for Civilian Crossings </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mostar Opens Checkpoint for Civilian Crossings </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0704192894 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0704192894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] There is some good news in Mostar today. A 
checkpoint has finally been opened for civilians to pass from 
one part of town to another and the work on normalizing the town 
infrastructure has begun. Here is a report by our Mostar 
correspondent Omer Vatric: 
  [Begin Vatric recording] This day will be remembered in 
Mostar by the first meetings of family members and friends at 
the town line of separation, at which only bullets and shells 
were meeting for a full 11 months. On two occasions, 50 Mostar 
people from the eastern and 50 from the western part of the town 
met at the crossroads in front of the burnt-down Hit department 
store. They were coming in groups of 25 and had two hours to 
tell about their pain, fear, and hope. [passage omitted] New 
groups of citizens should meet tomorrow as well as the next day. 
  The citizens of Donja Mahala, Semovac, and Sermica will 
remember this day because the water came back. Water 
authorities say that, in conformity with agreements reached with 
the Croatian Defense Council, these districts will get drinking 
water after more than nine months. Unfortunately, the entire 
left bank [of the Neretva] will remain without water in the 
coming days, and the entire eastern part of Mostar will remain 
without electricity. Constant talks about the implementation of 
the Washington agreement and implementing the agreed federation 
bring hope that all of Mostar will have water and electricity 
soon and that the building of bridges and a general 
normalization of life will begin. [passage omitted] [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

