<F P=103> AU0704183694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] We have received the following announcement by the 
Press Center of the Army of Bosnia-Herzegovina: 
  On 7 April 1994, beginning at 1800, Army General Rasim Delic 
issued the order to units of the Army of the Republic of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina on a general cease-fire with the Serbian 
aggressor's side to last 24 hours. This order ensued as a result 
of the insistence of the Security Council and Mr. Akashi in 
order to create necessary conditions for military-political 
talks with the representatives of the Serbian aggressor. The 
order issued to the units of the Army of the Republic of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina fully implies meeting the demands presented 
by representatives of the Army of the Republic of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. This above all applies to stopping the 
offensive of the Serbian aggressor's forces on Gorazde and 
Bihac, which was presented to General Rose and the public during 
the day. 

