<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cooperation Talks With FYROM Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cooperation Talks With FYROM Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0804171294 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1300 
GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0804171294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 8 April, at the Council of Ministers, a working 
meeting took place between governmental delegations of the 
Republic of Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia 
-- FYROM] and the Republic of Bulgaria, led by Deputy Prime 
Ministers Jovan Andonov and Valentin Karabashev, the Government 
Press Center reports. 
  Implementing the 1993 agreements between the two countries 
and the updated protocol signed on 15 March in Sofia was 
discussed. The delegations also discussed certain problems 
regarding the transit of goods through our country, improving 
the handling capacity of the border checkpoints, constructing a 
railroad between Gyueshevo and Kumanovo, and improving 
cooperation between the oil refineries of the two republics. 
  A readiness exists to sign soon in Skopje agreements on 
avoiding double taxation and mutual protection and encouragement 
of investments. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

