<H3> <TI>   Pawlak, Klaus Hold Cooperation Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pawlak, Klaus Hold Cooperation Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1004133394 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1144 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1004133394 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Jelenia Gora, 10 Apr--The prime ministers of 
Poland and the Czech Republic, Waldemar Pawlak and Vaclav Klaus, 
met today at Czocha Castle, near Lesna in the Jelenia Gora 
Voivodship to discuss cooperation between the two countries. 
  Ewa Wachowicz, press assistant to Prime Minister Pawlak, 
told 
a PAP journalist that this is a continuation of the talks 
commenced in Prague during the course of the visit there by U.S. 
President Bill Clinton. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

