<F P=101> Federal </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia To Urge UN To Lift FRY Sanctions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia To Urge UN To Lift FRY Sanctions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804132394 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1145 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0804132394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jagodina, 8 Apr (TANJUG) -- Democratic Party 
Chairman Zoran Djindjic told Jagodina Radio today that Russia 
will raise the issue of lifting the sanctions against the 
Federal Republic of Yugoslavia at the UN Security Council within 
a month. 
  "During our visit to Russia we drafted a request, which 
expresses joint views of all leading Russian parties as regards 
Yugoslavia, demanding that the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of 
the Russian Federation raise the issue of lifting the sanctions 
at the UN Security Council," Djindjic said, adding that he had 
received assurances that a majority in the parliament would vote 
for this document, about which the Yugoslav public will be 
informed either today or tomorrow. 
  "Russians have a clear interest to show their teeth to the 
West on the example of Yugoslavia, and to show that Russia has 
not lost the position of a superpower. They will do it not 
because of the Serbs, but because of Russia," Djindjic said. 

</TEXT>

