<F P=101> Serbia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbian Party Denounces NATO Air Strike </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbian Party Denounces NATO Air Strike </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1004201494 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1949 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1004201494 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 10 Apr (TANJUG) -- The Democratic Party of 
Serbia said this evening that "the bombing of the Serb positions 
around Gorazde shows yet again that the international community, 
whose position is almost always voiced by its most powerful 
members, resorts to the worst possible course of action to reach 
peace in the former Bosnia-Herzgovina." 
  The statement says that daily UN Protection Force reports 
from the ground, as well as media reports, showed that the 
fighting around Gorazde was provoked by the Muslim forces and 
also that it was on a limited scale. 
  "In spite of this NATO, or rather those who irresponsibly 
pull its strings, showed with this attack against the Serb 
positions that they have war and not peace on their mind, and 
that they are not impartial but support one side in the 
conflict." 
  "The Democratic Party of Serbia regrets that the 
international community, having betrayed the role of a mediator, 
has through this action become a participant in the civil war in 
the former Bosnia-Herzegovina," the statement says. 

</TEXT>

