<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fighting, Situation Around Gorazde Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fighting, Situation Around Gorazde Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Serb Forces `Liberate' Villages </H4>

<F P=102> LD1004111894 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1001 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1004111894 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cajnice, 10 Apr (TANJUG) -- The command of the 
Herzegovina Corps today announced that Serb fighters liberated 
the villages of Cindici and Zupcici, south of Gorazde, in 
yesterday's actions. By liberating these two villages 
conditions have been created for units of the Herzegovina Corps 
to take control of these important Muslim strongholds in the 
area around Uhotic Hill and Bukovo plain, the last remaining 
Muslim strongholds on the right bank of the Drina, upstream from 
Gorazde. 
  In order to prevent the withdrawal of members of the 31st 
Brigade of the so-called army of Bosnia-Herzegovina, who 
suffered a major military defeat in the Cindici area, their 
command ordered that the bridge in this village be destroyed. 
  The command of the Herzegovina Corps claims that Serb army 
units engaged in a counteroffensive from the Visegrad direction 
are deployed just outside Kopaci, six km downstream from Gorazde. 
  Serb military sources say that the Muslim army is still 
concentrating its forces in the area around Gradina, Volujaca 
and Uhotic Hill and that its members -- according to an 
imprisoned Muslim soldier -- have been threatened with death if 
they lose these strategic points. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-8056 </DOCNO>
