<H3> <TI>   Fighting, Situation Around Gorazde Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fighting, Situation Around Gorazde Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Muslim Army Stronghold Captured </H4>

<F P=102> LD1004131594 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1147 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1004131594 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cajnice, 10 Apr (TANJUG) -- Serb fighters this 
morning liberated Uhotici Brdo, one of the last Muslim army 
strongholds south of Gorazde, the command of the Herzegovina 
Corps reported. 
  Units of the Serb Republic Army are reported to be in 
control 
of the right bank of the Drina from Vitkovici to Dzindici at a 
distance of about 700 meters from the river. 
  NATO planes are breaking the sound barrier while flying at 
low level above the area between Gorazde, Foca and Cajnice -- 
the scene of heavy fighting over the past 13 days. 
  The command of the Hercegovina Corps, denying Muslim media 
reports, said today that Serb fighters have not engaged in any 
military actions in the center of Gorazde. 

</TEXT>

