<H4>    Serb Troops Crossing Drina River </H4>

<F P=102> AU1004135394 Paris AFP in English 1345 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1004135394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Zagreb, April 10 (AFP) -- Bosnian Serb troops on 
Sunday began crossing the Drina river just south of the besieged 
Moslem town of Gorazde following a massive artillery offensive, 
the UN High Commissioner for Refugees announced. 
  The soldiers began crossing the river shortly after 3:00 
p.m. 
(1300 GMT), the UNHCR spokesman in Zagreb, Peter Kessler said. 
  The river had marked the front line between the warring 
forces. 

</TEXT>

