<H4>    Serb Tanks Roll Into Town </H4>

<F P=102> AU1004164894 Paris AFP in English 1648 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1004164894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, April 10 (AFP) -- Bosnian Serb forces took 
control Sunday of the riverbank where the Moslem town of Gorazde 
is located, and Serb tanks rolled into the southern part of 
town, the United Nations said. 
  UN spokesman Dacre Halloway said the Serb forces took over 
the bank after crossing the Drina river, which had been the 
frontline between the two warring parties. He said there was 
sniper fire outside the office of the UN High Commissioner for 
Refugees. 
  Serb forces have been attacking the Gorazde enclave for the 
past two weeks. 

</TEXT>

