<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fighting, Situation Around Gorazde Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fighting, Situation Around Gorazde Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Explosives Planted in Factory </H4>

<F P=102> LD1004173394 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1004173394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Is Gorazde going to be another Bhopal? After 13 
days of fighting [words indistinct] the defenders from the area 
of Vitkovici decided to plant explosives in a nitrogen factory. 
We have just learned from Mirsad Dragolj that explosives were 
planted in two tanks containing 25 metric tons of ammonia each 
and a tank with 20 tons of formalin. 
  If these tanks explode, the consequences would certainly be 
vast, not only for the area of Vitkovici and Gorazde, but also 
for the whole of the northern part of the Drina valley. Mr. 
Dragolj said this was not an act of desperation, but a move 
caused by futile actions of the representatives of the 
peacekeeping forces. It is a consequence of the lies about the 
latest offensive by some key people in the world organization 
and also of the reactions by our state and military organs, 
which came too late. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

