<H4>    NATO Warplanes Strike Serb Positions </H4>

<F P=102> AU1004174894 Paris AFP in English 1748 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1004174894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brussels, April 10 (AFP) -- NATO warplanes Sunday 
carried out airstrikes over the Serb-besieged Moslem town of 
Gorazde in Bosnia-Herzegovina, a NATO spokesman said here. 
  The North Atlantic Treaty Organisation carried out the 
attacks at the request of UN forces, the spokesman said. 
  Serb forces were Sunday pressing home an attack on Gorazde 
after a massive artillery barrage following a two-week siege. 
  The ongoing attacks against Serb positions by two NATO F-16C 
aircraft were confirmed in the Bosnian capital Sarajevo by UN 
Protection Force spokesman Major Dacre Halloway. 

</TEXT>

