<H4>    NATO Details Bombing </H4>

<F P=102> AU1004190194 Paris AFP in English 1851 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1004190194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Sarajevo, April 10 (AFP) -- Two NATO warplanes 
on Sunday carried out air strikes against Bosnian Serb positions 
around the besieged Moslem town of Gorazde, following a major 
Serb offensive, a UN military spokesman said here. [passage 
omitted] 
  The warplanes dropped bombs using UNPROFOR air-to-ground 
guidance systems and "provided close air support to United 
Nations personnel in Gorazde," the NATO Southern Command 
announced in Naples, Italy. [passage omitted] 
  NATO officials in Naples said the air attack occurred around 
6:22 p.m. (1622 GMT). "Battle damage assessment is underway," 
NATO announced. [passage omitted] 
  The NATO spokesman in Brussels said further details would be 
made available after consultation with military authorities. 
[passage omitted] 

