<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fighting, Situation Around Gorazde Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Shelling Continues Despite Air Strike </H4>

<F P=102> LD1004205494 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 2000 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1004205494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Fahrudin Becic from Gorazde] </F>
  [Excerpts] Several questions are being raised in Gorazde: 
Are the chetniks really going to enter the town, will Mirsad 
Dragolj [not further identified] blow up the nitrogen factory 
(?despite the fact) that the U.S. Phantoms [as received] have 
bombed the Chetnik positions. 
  It is impossible to give precise answers to any of these 
questions. Since 1700 two Phantoms have been flying over the 
Gorazde area. We do not have valid information about their 
actions, but according to some reports from the ground, strong 
explosions were heard 13 kilometers southwest of the town center. 
  Since the attacks against the territory on the right bank of 
the Drina River have been organized and carried out from there 
in the last 13 days, it seems possible that the report on the 
Phantoms' actions is true. 
  This, however, did not stop the Chetnik forces continuing 
[word indistinct] toward the center. Some eye-witnesses claim 
that the Chetniks even shot at the planes. 
  The part of the town on the right bank on the Drina River 
has 
been evacuated. The town was again heavily shelled this 
evening. There were fatalities and wounded in several suburbs. 
Chetnik snipers fired on the town center and around the UNHCR 
[UN High Commissioner for Refugees] offices. 
  Heavy small-arms fighting is under way on the approaches to 
the town. Some people have been killed and wounded. [passage 
omitted] 
  Around 2030 the howitzer-shelling of the town center 
intensified. Unfortunately, there were fatalities again. I am 
afraid that the casualty toll today is extremely high. Gorazde 
is entering the most uncertain night in its long history. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

