<H4>    Permanent Squadron To Be Installed </H4>

<F P=102> LD1004204994 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 2026 GMT 
10 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1004204994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The two American F-16 fighters, which this afternoon 
attacked Serb positions around the town of Gorazde, have 
returned safely to the U.S. Air Force base at Aviano in 
northeast Italy. 
  In the meantime it has been revealed that the two planes 
were 
flying a reconaissence mission over Bosnia when they received 
the order -- using a secret code -- to intervene in Gorazde. 
  Tomorrow a permanent intervention squadron will be installed 
at Aviano, the first of its type at an Italian airbase. 

</TEXT>

