<H4>    Izetbegovic Receives Redman </H4>

<F P=102> LD1004214594 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 2100 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1004214594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Presidency Alija 
Izetbegovic today received U.S. President Clinton's special 
envoy Charles Redman regarding the most dramatic situation in 
Gorazde. The talks were also attended by Bosnia-Herzegovina 
Premier Haris Silajdzic and U.S. Ambassador to 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Victor Jakovich. 
  The situation in Gorazde is critical indeed. We are 
examining the problem very seriously, and I hope the necessary 
steps will be taken. This is all I can tell you, Redman said 
following the meeting. 
  Asked by reporters whether the ferocity of the fighting has 
subsided following the threat of air strikes unless an end is 
put to the offensive, Redman says: This was in the morning [as 
heard]. Since noon the situation has changed and become very 
serious due to Serb advances. 
  Turkish President Demirel talked over the phone with 
Izetbegovic late this afternoon. President Demirel called 
President Izetbegovic to tell him that Turkey would do its best 
to initiate actions that would provide protection for the 
citizens of Gorazde. 

</TEXT>

