<H4>    Want Negotiations Only With Churkin </H4>

<F P=102> LD1104142094 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1349 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1104142094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Novi Sad, 11 Apr (TANJUG) -- Momcilo Krajisnik, 
president of the people's assembly of the Srpska republic of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, today told Novi Sad Radio that following the 
bombardment of the Serb forces around Gorazde negotiations with 
UN representatives would only be conducted through Russian 
special envoy Vitaliy Churkin. 
  Krajisnik added that the Srpska republic of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina no longer trusted other mediators since they 
had been abusing the trust of the top leadership of the Srpska 
republic. 
  Krajisnik also pointed out that it was a totally obvious 
fact 
that the Muslim forces had provoked the Serbs around Gorazde to 
shatter the cessation of hostilities and an agreement on peace. 
Instead of the Muslim forces bearing responsibility for the 
conflicts around Gorazde, the NATO aircraft bombed the positions 
of Serb units near Gorazde. 

</TEXT>

