<H4>    Serb Attack Continues </H4>

<F P=102> AU1104115994 Paris AFP in English 1148 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1104115994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Geneva, April 11 (AFP) -- Bosnian Serbs on Monday 
continued shelling the mainly Moslem town of Gorazde, reportedly 
injuring some 200 people, a UN High Commissioner for Refugees 
(UNHCR) spokeswoman said here. 
  Shells hit a school that was being used as a refugee centre 
and some 200 people were said to be injured, Christiane 
Berthiaume said, citing reports from four UNHCR personnel in the 
Moslem enclave in Bosnia-Herzegovina. 

</TEXT>

