<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Fierce' Inter-Muslim Clashes Reported in West </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Fierce' Inter-Muslim Clashes Reported in West </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1004172394 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1705 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1004172394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Petrovac, April 10 (TANJUG) -- Inter-Moslem clashes 
on Sunday continued at unabated intensity along all demarcation 
lines in the Cazin Krajina, in western Bosnia-Herzegovina, 
Moslem media in the Bihac region reported. 
  Forces of the Autonomous Province of Western Bosnia (APWB), 
proclaimed last September, are successfully repelling a fresh 
offensive by members of the 5th Corps of the Moslem Army, loyal 
to hardline leader Alija Izetbegovic, the Western Bosnian News 
Agency ZBIA said. 
  Moslem-controlled radio in Bihac said that both sides 
reported casualties and the missing during Sunday's fightings in 
the Cazin Krajina. This was also confirmed by the Moslem Radio 
Sarajevo. 
  The Moslem Army command, loyal to Izetbegovic, has admitted 
that 500 people were killed and over 2,000 wounded during eight 
months of fighting with the APWB forces, loyal to Izetbegovic's 
rival Fikret Abdic who opposes Izetbegovic policy of war. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

