<F P=106> [Report by Armonko Grgic for Herceg-Bosna from Busovaca] </F>
  [Excerpt] The police station in Busovaca has informed us 
that a bus full of civilians that left Busovaca for Kiseljak at 
0930 was turned back from the joint checkpoint in the village of 
Brestovsko in the Kiseljak municipality because the Muslim side 
would not let it through to Croat-held territory. The Muslims 
said that the HVO [Croatian Defense Council] would not allow 
free movement of humanitarian aid convoys to the Muslim side. 
All this was caused by an incident in Kresevo where a Muslim 
sniper killed an HVO soldier. The road between Busovaca and 
Kiseljak was opened three days ago. [passage omitted] 

