<F P=102>   LD1104090294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 0737 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1104090294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brcko, 11 Apr (TANJUG) -- Early this morning, Muslim 
forces launched a heavy combined mortar and infantry attack from 
the direction of Pejici and Pejina, seven kilometers south of 
Brcko. They attacked Serb positions in the areas of Ulice, 
Lukici, and Lipovac, Serb military sources have announced. 
  More than 20 60-mm and 82-mm mortar shells were fired on the 
Serb defense lines, followed by fierce fire from infantry 
weapons. 
  Members of the Serb republic army responded to the attack, 
after which there has been a lull in this section of the 
Posavlje [River Sava valley] battlefield. 
  Last night and this morning was mainly quiet on the Gradacac 
and Orasje battlefronts [northern Bosnia]. 

</TEXT>

