<H3> <TI>   Muslims Capture Serb Prisoners in Tarcin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Muslims Capture Serb Prisoners in Tarcin </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1004205994 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 2000 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1004205994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The dramatic situation in Gorazde has been 
reflected on the events in Tarcin. Our correspondent from Tarcin 
has sent us this report: 
  All access roads to Tarcin are still blocked. According to 
reports we have received so far, the situation is becoming 
increasingly complex according to Bosnia-Hercegovina radio 
broadcasts about the dramatic situation at the Gorazde 
battlefield. At the first roadblock in Tarcin, we have learned 
that despite all measures carried out by police forces of the 
Hadzici public security station, soldiers of the Fifth Hill 
Brigade, and members of the antiterrorist squad, embittered 
citizens from eastern Bosnia [Muslim refugees] and the local 
people expressing solidarity with their demands have seized 
silos in which the arrested aggressor soldiers are being held. 
  Judging by the shots we heard fired from infantry weapons, 
the Tarcin drama culminated this evening. This was immediately 
followed by sirens of ambulance cars in Tarcin. However, we 
still have not received any details about casualties. We are 
unable to get details because Tarcin is completely blocked. 
[passage omitted] 
  As we are filing this report, we have just received a report 
that police forces and members of the antiterrorist squad have 
seized the control of the silo prison again. However, the 
protesters have taken three aggressor soldiers in an unknown 
direction. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

