<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   RSK Assembly Ratifies Cease-Fire Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    RSK Assembly Ratifies Cease-Fire Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804151294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1426 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0804151294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Knin, 8 Apr (TANJUG) -- Following today's lengthy 
discussions the assembly of the republic of Serb Krajina 
unanimously ratified the Zagreb agreement on a cease-fire and 
the separation of Serb and Croatian forces. 
  Winding up the discussion Assembly Speaker Branko Vojnica 
described the agreement as a constructive step in the 
negotiating process toward the restoration of peace. 
  The Assembly tasked a delegation of the republic of Serb 
Krajina to the so-called second phase of negotiations referring 
to economic and humanitarian cooperation not to accept talks on 
issues which could prejudice political solutions. 
  As the second phase of negotiations with the Croatian side 
is 
yet to begin, the assembly decided that these negotiations be 
led by a new Krajina government, which is to be formed in about 
10 days. 
  The Krajina parliament also unanimously decided that all 
agreements and treaties reached in negotiations with Croatia are 
subject to ratification by the assembly. The assembly session 
continues. 

</TEXT>

