<F P=106> [Report by Danko Peric from Knin] </F>
  [Text] Lieutenant Colonel Marinko Gajic, assistant 
commander of the General Staff of the Serbian Army of Krajina, 
has said that members of infantry units had withdrawn by 0900. 
There have been minor problems in western Slavonia and the 
assistant commander of the Serbian Army of Krajina expects them 
to be solved during the day. So far, nothing has been heard from 
UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces], whose units are going to be 
deployed between Krajina and Croatian infantry units who have 
moved apart by one kilometer each. 
  The first meeting of the central joint commission, attended 
by Lieutenant General Bertrand De Lapresle, UNPROFOR commander 
for the former Yugoslavia, is under way in Turanj, near Karlovac. 
  The second meeting of the first session of the republican 
assembly is under way in Knin at the moment. It has been 
learned that the report by the negotiating team to the peace 
negotiations held in the Russian Embassy in Zagreb is also going 
to be discussed at the session. It has also been learned that 
the proposal on prime minister designate and the new government 
had been taken off the agenda and that this is most probably 
going to be discussed on 20 April. 

</TEXT>

