<H3> <TI>   Krajina's Mikelic Names Deputy Prime Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Krajina's Mikelic Names Deputy Prime Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804155194 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1456 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0804155194 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kragujevac, 8 Apr (TANJUG) -- Borisav Mikelic, 
Krajina prime minister-designate, stated today that full 
agreement had been reached with the Democratic Party of Krajina 
on a government of national unity. 
  He told Kragujevac Radio that Milan Babic would be appointed 
deputy prime minister and minister of foreign affairs, and in 
the next few days more details would be disclosed regarding 
ministers and departments of the new Krajina Government. 
  Stressing that the basic aim was now to include in 
production 
those people returning from the front, Mikelic said there would 
be no place for war profiteers in Krajina. 
  "We shall fight them with all means at our disposal, 
primarily the means of a law-governed state," Mikelic said. 

